Comment: This game i played "Birds Opening" A reversal of the "Dutch" for black. Although f4 is not necessarily whites strongest opening move, And rarely seen at the top level, I feel as though it leads to an exciting game and a very enjoyable game at that.

This move came as quite a surprise, My opponent developed his light squared bishop only to trade it at first chance. Better would of been to continue with normal developing principles such as Nf6 or Nc6 . Also Castling king side is whites idea. So blacks light squared bishop would of been perfectly placed.
